Package org.opentosca.toscana.model.capability

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AdminEndpointCapability
    The default TOSCA type that should be used or extended to define a specialized administrator endpoint capability.
    AttachmentCapability
    Defines an attachment capability of a (logical) infrastructure device node (e.g., BlockStorage node).
    BindableCapability
    A node that has the BindableCapability indicates that it can be bound to a logical network association via a network port.
    Capability
    Defines a set of data that can be associated with a RootNode to describe its capability or feature.
    ComputeCapability
    Indicates that the node can provide hosting on a named compute resource.
    ContainerCapability
    The ContainerCapability indicates that the node can act as a container (or a host) for one or more other declared Node Types.
    DatabaseEndpointCapability
    The default TOSCA type that should be used or extended to define a specialized database endpoint capability.
    DockerContainerCapability
    The type indicates capabilities of a Docker runtime environment (client).
    EndpointCapability
    This is the default type that should be used or extended to define a network endpoint capability.
    NetworkCapability
    The NetworkCapability indicates that the node can provide addressability for the resource within a network.
    NodeCapability
    The NodeCapability indicates the base capabilities of a TOSCA Node Type.
    OsCapability
    The default TOSCA type to express an Operating System capability for a node.
    PublicEndpointCapability
    Represents a public endpoint which is accessible to the general internet (and its public IP address ranges).
    ScalableCapability
    The default TOSCA type that should be used to express a scalability capability of a node.
    StorageCapability
    The StorageCapability indicates that the node can provide a named storage location with specified size range.
